: "Will Robinson-Smith", "socials": null}], "url": "https://spaceflightnow.com/2026/03/13/live-coverage-spacex-to-launch-friday-morning-starlink-mission-from-cape-canaveral/", "image_url": "http://spaceflightnow.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/20241022_Starlink_6-61_prelaunch_AB-1-678x445.jpg", "news_site": "Spaceflight Now", "summary": "The Starlink 10-48 mission will add another 29 broadband internet satellites to the company\u2019s constellation in low Earth orbit. Liftoff from pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station is scheduled for 8:10 a.m. EDT (1210 UTC).", "published_at": "2026-03-13T02:08:35Z", "updated_at": "2026-03-13T07:30:35.680922Z", "featured": false, "launches": [{"launch_id": "6f2868b8-1000-48e5-893b-700c1371b4fb", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}], "events": []}, {"id": 36821, "title": "NASA Now Targeting April 1 for Artemis II\u2019s Launch Around The Moon", "authors": [{"name": "Marcia Smith", "socials": null}], "url": "https://spacepolicyonline.com/news/nasa-now-targeting-april-1-for-artemis-ii-launch-around-the-moon/", "image_url": "https://spacepolicyonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Artemis-2-April-dates-297x300.jpg", "news_site": "SpacePolicyOnline.com", "summary": "NASA announced today they are targeting April 1 at 6:24 pm Eastern Daylight Time for sending the Artemis II crew around the Moon. In preparation, their Space Launch System rocket [\u2026]", "published_at": "2026-03-12T22:38:00Z", "updated_at": "2026-03-13T07:30:24.569372Z", "featured": false, "launches": [{"launch_id": "41699701-2ef4-4b0c-ac9d-6757820cde87", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}], "events": []}, {"id": 36819, "title": "China\u2019s Tianwen-3 Mars sample return mission moves into spacecraft construction phase", "authors": [{"name": "Andrew Jones", "socials": null}], "url": "https://spacenews.com/chinas-tianwen-3-mars-sample-return-mission-moves-into-spacecraft-construction-phase/", "image_url": "https://i0.wp.com/spacenews.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/mars-nort